# Document Management System вҖ” Implementation Plan

A production-grade Document Management System for the LDM College ERP that lets Admin/Teachers dynamically create document requirements (Aadhaar, marksheets, assignments, etc.), assign them to students/batches/programs, and manage a full upload вҶ’ review вҶ’ approve/reject workflow.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **File Storage Strategy:** Currently the project uses **local filesystem** (`public/uploads/`) for library documents and **Cloudinary** for gallery media. For student document uploads (Aadhaar, marksheets, etc.), I plan to use **Cloudinary** with `resource_type: 'raw'` to keep files secure, cloud-backed, and not publicly accessible via the filesystem. This is production-ready. Let me know if you prefer local storage instead.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Teacher Access:** The plan gives Teachers the ability to create **assignment-type** requirements (linked to their subjects) and review submissions for their own assignments. Only Admin can create personal document requirements (Aadhaar, marksheets). Let me know if you want teachers to have broader or narrower access.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Database Layer

#### [NEW] [DocumentRequirement.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/DocumentRequirement.ts)

The "template" model вҖ” defines *what* documents are needed and *who* needs to submit them.

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `title` | String | e.g. "Aadhaar Card", "Assignment 3" |
| `description` | String | Instructions for the student |
| `category` | Enum | `personal_document` \| `academic` \| `assignment` \| `certificate` |
| `required_file_types` | String[] | Allowed extensions: `['pdf', 'jpg', 'png']` |
| `max_file_size_mb` | Number | e.g. 5 |
| `is_mandatory` | Boolean | Whether submission is required |
| `due_date` | Date | Optional deadline |
| `scope.type` | Enum | `all` \| `program` \| `batch` \| `student` |
| `scope.program` | ObjectId вҶ’ Program | If scoped to a program |
| `scope.batch` | ObjectId вҶ’ Batch | If scoped to a batch |
| `scope.students` | ObjectId[] вҶ’ User | If assigned to specific students |
| `subject` | ObjectId вҶ’ Subject | For assignment-type requirements |
| `created_by` | ObjectId вҶ’ User | Admin or Teacher who created it |
| `is_active` | Boolean | Soft toggle |

**Indexes:** `{ category: 1, is_active: 1 }`, `{ 'scope.program': 1 }`, `{ 'scope.batch': 1 }`

---

#### [NEW] [DocumentSubmission.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/DocumentSubmission.ts)

The "submission" model вҖ” tracks each student's upload and its review status.

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `requirement` | ObjectId вҶ’ DocumentRequirement | Which requirement this fulfills |
| `student` | ObjectId вҶ’ User | Who submitted |
| `file_url` | String | Cloudinary URL |
| `file_name` | String | Original filename |
| `file_type` | String | `pdf`, `jpg`, `png`, `docx` |
| `file_size` | Number | Bytes |
| `cloudinary_public_id` | String | For deletion/management |
| `status` | Enum | `pending` \| `approved` \| `rejected` \| `resubmitted` |
| `review` | Object | `{ reviewed_by, reviewed_at, comment }` |
| `submission_history` | Array | `[{ file_url, submitted_at, status, comment }]` вҖ” tracks all versions |
| `submitted_at` | Date | Latest submission timestamp |

**Indexes:** `{ requirement: 1, student: 1 }` (unique compound вҖ” one submission per requirement per student), `{ student: 1, status: 1 }`

---

#### [MODIFY] [AuditLog.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/AuditLog.ts)

Add `'DocumentRequirement'` and `'DocumentSubmission'` to the `entityType` enum so all document actions are audit-logged.

