## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification (recommended approach)

Since the project has no automated test runner configured, I recommend manual testing the full workflow:

**Test 1 вҖ” Admin creates a requirement:**
1. Login as Admin at `ldmcollege.com`
2. Go to **Admin вҶ’ Documents** (new sidebar item)
3. Click **"Create Requirement"**
4. Fill: Title = "Aadhaar Card", Category = "Personal Document", Scope = "All Students", File Types = PDF/JPG
5. Verify it appears in the requirements table

**Test 2 вҖ” Student sees the requirement:**
1. Login as a Student
2. Go to **Student вҶ’ Documents** (new sidebar item)
3. Verify the "Aadhaar Card" requirement appears as "Not Submitted"

**Test 3 вҖ” Student uploads a document:**
1. Click "Upload" on the Aadhaar requirement
2. Select a PDF file under 5MB
3. Verify status changes to "Pending"

**Test 4 вҖ” Admin reviews submission:**
1. Login as Admin
2. Go to **Documents вҶ’ Submissions** tab
3. Find the student's submission
4. Click to review, download the file, add a comment, click "Approve"
5. Verify status changes to "Approved"

**Test 5 вҖ” Rejection and re-upload:**
1. Admin rejects a different submission with comment "Blurry photo, please re-upload"
2. Student sees the rejection reason and re-uploads
3. Verify old file is archived in history and new status = "Resubmitted"

**Test 6 вҖ” Role-based access:**
1. Try accessing `/admin/documents` as a Student вҶ’ should redirect to home
2. Try calling `/api/admin/documents/submissions` without auth вҶ’ should return 401
3. Verify teachers can only create `assignment` category requirements
